monday encouragement 🤎 

I’ve come to know that all my running, hiding + attempts of finding fulfillment in anything other than Christ has always left me empty + desiring more. 

but isn’t it just like grace to meet us there. I’ve come to know that I would have never known the fullness and precious presence of Christ if it wasn’t for the emptiness of the dark places. 

I used to wonder why things were the way they were. why that person left. why I just wasn’t enough in that situation. why I felt so alone in all the thoughts + confusion of how a loving god could just leave me in such a hurt place.

until he picked me up + reminded me that he is not only a gracious + loving father but he is also sovereign in and over everything that happens every second of everyday. that everything has its purpose + nothing is wasted. that what you walked through + what you are walking through is apart of divine purpose. 

whether you have walked through this or are walking through this, please understand that the lord is too good to be unkind + he is too wise to be mistaken. and in the moments where you can not understand how a loving god could lead you to a place of hurt + pain, remember you may not be able to understand everything but you can trust his heart because he will never lead you anywhere he hasn’t yet been and he will never let you walk alone. 

friend. you are seen in your hiding. chased down in your running + surely never alone in the confusion + questions.

“the Lord directs the steps of the godly. He delights in every detail of their lives. Though they stumble, they will never fall, for the LORD holds them by the hand. —  Psalm 37:23-24 

if he delights in the detail of my day to day so will I.  may our gaze ever be on his goodness. in the small moments of our day. in the details of those we encounter. the commute to work. the barista behind the counter. the sunlight shining through the window in the early mornings. the laughter of loved ones around a table. soak it in. all of it. never miss a moment to dance upon his goodness with a thankful heart. to just simply do life with Him. delight in the detail.

3 years today with my love. 

oh, the places we have been and the places we will go! being yours is my greatest joy. I love you very much!

“who among the gods is like you, Lord? who is like you —— majestic in holiness, awesome in glory, working wonders?” 
— Exodus 15:11 

I am brought to my knees in awe of our father. tears of joy fill my eyes when I think of the unfamiliar faces that have become family this week. my heart is overjoyed when I look at His faithfulness in and through the lives of these students. the kindness of His heart 😭 I am simply overwhelmed.

leading beside the wonderful women I now call friends @jadee.wolfe + @laurieshearman has been the most precious thing to me. watching their consistency, pursuit and burning passion for the lord this week fills my heart. to know them is to love them. to stand beside them is a joy I simply can not express through words. I’m just so so grateful + expectant for what the lord is doing in + through His people! 

have our everything, Lord Jesus. may our lives be a drink offering ever pouring for you only. take ALL of me.

quite mornings sitting and dwelling in His presence. my heart is filled with gratitude by His goodness + beauty that greets me every morning I rise + every evening I lay my head. 

the past few weeks I have been wrecked by His presence. A group of ladies I have the joy of calling friends have been walking through the discipline of silence + solitude. Practicing stilling our minds before the king + making room for Him in our daily lives, whether that be 5 minutes or 5 hours of our day. my goodness, have I been met by Him. from soaking in His presence in the cozy corners of my home to afternoon walks in the sunshine crying before him + letting him have my heart again + again. 

I often make the excuse that I’m “too busy” to walk with Him. to sit with Him. to make time for Him. but as I have stepped deeper into knowing Him + locking my eyes upon Him, I am reminded over + over that as time goes by + seasons change and I often find myself lost in the busy + hurry of life, I can always find myself right here, in love so safe. 🤍

——— my days have felt so lovely + sweet recently. slowing down + cherishing all the precious moments. squeezing those around me alittle tighter, laughing alittle harder + falling more in love of Jesus in every passing moment. ✨🥹☀️🫶🏼☺️

I always have the best quiet time when I’m sitting by the ocean. today I was reminded that if you continue to receive validation and approval from people around you, you will live an empty + exhausting life. stop living to chase the approval of others + step into the life you were always called to live. 

there is too much about you that is so lovely + beautiful + just amazing. what a shame to live trying to prove your worth to those around you + be somebody you are not. be who you are. stop changing yourself to impress others. stop trying to say the right things to make them like you. don’t live a life that is leading by fear + hyper focused on the opinions of others, rather live in the freedom to be who you really are and know that that is more than enough. you are so loved, sister! start living that way!

for the college girl who….. 

feels like she is trying her best to hold it all together. wrestling in a season of singleness. drowning in a relationship that is not god’s best for her. battling the pressure of perfection + striving to be good enough. feels like she is searching far + wide for community, but can’t seem to belong anywhere. 

 I want to remind you that you are not alone. all the nights you struggle to fall asleep because your mind is running through your list of things you have yet to step into. all the times you find yourself in a crowded room, feeling completely alone. the singleness. the relationship that is stealing your joy. the dark moments that leave you broken hearted + confused. Jesus meets you. whether you see it or not. wether you feel it or not. He meets you there. He gives you the gift of a sound mind + stands behind, before + beside you in the moments you feel like you are the only person in the world. He does not abandon you, nor does He stand at a distance in moments where your pain is too much to handle. 

He is not afraid of the way you feel. He is not distant in times you are desperate for His nearness. He draws near. + maybe. just maybe. in the moments we feel most alone. in the moments we feel as though we are grasping for air. those may just be the moments, that if we abandon our fear of losing our ability to control every step and release our pain to Him, we may just find that He was the answer + the fullness to everything we have been longing for.

to the college girl who feels like she can’t get a break, you are going to make it. I know because this was me. + in the middle of my mess He met me every time, + called me closer to a love that I had been searching for in all the wrong places. 

don’t let college be a place you lose yourself in all the things you were told would give you life, rather lose yourself in His love, and daily surrender the moments that you just can’t handle on your own.

passion 2024. 

I may never find the words to express all that happened in these days. I fall to my knees in gratitude for the gift it is to witness + be apart of these holy moments. Lord, you are so good.

—— people often ask me what I love most about harry, or what drew me to him from the very beginning, and although I can spend forever talking about all the things I love about my sweet harry, the first thing that always comes to mind is this: he has always treated me with the utmost gentleness + loving kindness. 

from the moment I met harry, I knew him to be someone who was a true friend to any and all. someone who made everybody feel like a somebody. and from then to now, a kind soul and gentle heart who has continually loved me through + through. there is a lot I hold dear to my heart about this sweet man, but one thing I simply can never lose sight of is that he is oh so gentle and kind. I love him more with time and grow in awe of jesus for this gift!
